SEC. 3. The Tublay School of Home Industries shall:

a. Offer courses in home and/or cottage industries, particularly those that can avail of and best utilize the supply of raw materials available in the locality and enrollment shall be open to all, including adults;

b. Conduct researches on designing and processing of materials that are found in the locality and in the Province of Benguet and engage in producing models of handtools and small equipment and machineries for training and production;;

c. Undertake the standardization of craft promotion;

d. Render consultant services in home industries promotion and technology and conduct extension training throughout the Province of Benquet;

e. Offer courses in secondary and technical levels with home industries as the core.

SEC. 4. The Tublay School of Home Industries is hereto authorized to accept endowments, land grants, donations or contributions from provincial and municipal governments, private citizens, agencies and entities whether government or private for the improvement and expansion of its services.
